<repos>
Read the repos library from `/Users/bernard/.claude/projects/-Users-bernard-polymarket-bot/memory/reference_github_repos.md`.

Based on the user's input:

- **No args (`/repos`)**: Display the full library, organized by category headers. Use clean markdown with clickable links.
- **With category (`/repos sdks`, `/repos bots`, `/repos data`, etc.)**: Filter to just that category section.
- **`/repos add <github-url>`**: 
  1. Fetch the URL with WebFetch to get repo description
  2. Determine the best category (SDKs, Bots, Data, Platforms, AI, Curated Lists — or create a new one if none fit)
  3. Append the repo to the appropriate section in the memory file
  4. Update MEMORY.md if needed
  5. Confirm to the user
- **`/repos search <keyword>`**: Search across all repo names and descriptions for the keyword.

Keep output concise. Show repos as `- [owner/repo](url) — description` format.
</repos>
